        <section>
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>Hire-purchase credit allows individuals and businesses to acquire property through structured, periodic payments, while ownership transfers after the final payment. FSTL has facilitated hire-purchase schemes for over two decades, enabling real estate access to low- and middle-income Nigerians.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Key Benefits</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Enables property acquisition without requiring full upfront payment.</li>
                <li>Supports the development of middle-class housing and SME real estate projects.</li>
                <li>Encourages disciplined repayment culture, strengthening the overall credit system.</li>
                <li>Reduces risks for lenders while maintaining borrower flexibility.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>FSTL Approach</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Property verification and title checks integrated with hire-purchase agreements.</li>
                <li>Customised payment plans for diverse income levels and property types.</li>
                <li>Linkage with mortgage insurance and title guarantee for complete risk management.</li>
                <li>Guidance for financial institutions on structuring hire-purchase portfolios.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Economic Impact</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Increases housing affordability and access for middle-income earners.</li>
                <li>Strengthens credit culture and formal financial engagement.</li>
                <li>Facilitates property market expansion and liquidity for lenders.</li>
                <li>Supports national housing deficit reduction targets and land industrialisation.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
